# REDUCE_FLAT -*-perl-*-

=head1 NAME

REDUCE_FLAT

=head1 AUTHORS

Frossie Economou <frossie@jach.hawaii.edu>
Paul Hirst <p.hirst@jach.hawaii.edu>

=head1 DESCIPTION

Reduces a flat field in the conventional manner, including
normalisation by a model of the blackbody source. Files the normalised
flat field frame for use by subsequent flat fielding operations.

=cut

_SPECTROSCOPY_HELLO_
_ADD_READNOISE_VARIANCE_
_SUBTRACT_BIAS_
_ADD_POISSON_VARIANCE_
_INTERLEAVE_DETECTOR_POSITIONS_
_COADD_MULTIPLE_EXPOSURES_
_WAVELENGTH_CALIBRATE_BY_ESTIMATION_
_NORMALISE_FLAT_BY_BB_
_FILE_FLAT_SPECT_
